deck: The Fisher King former leader of N.E.M.O.
description:
Current Events

N.E.M.O. is currently under the control of Black Manta and his second in command Black Jack.

Creation

Fisher King was created by writer Dan Abnett and penciler Philippe Briones in Aquaman #5.

Major Story Arcs

The Drowning

Fisher King was the leader of N.E.M.O., a secret society covertly controlling the oceans since 1983. He tried to recruit Black Manta as an agent but when they disagreed Manta murdered him by slicing his throat in front of N.E.M.O., before anyone could react. Black Manta then seized control of the organization, with Black Jack as his second in command.

Powers & Abilities

FIsher King does not possess any superhuman powers, but as the leader of an extremely wealthy secret society he has access to many resources.

Leadership

Fisher King was the leader of an enormous secret organization with global power.

Intelect

Fisher King is a clever leader and his organization has been covertly controling the oceans and trade by seas since 1983.

Weapons/Equipment

Great Wealth

As the head of N.E.M.O. he has ammassed a great fortune that allows for global power and influence as well as furthering N.E.M.O.'s agenda

Advanced Technology

N.E.M.O. possesses highly advanced technology like their Albatross Stealth Planes. Fisher King is seen resting on a floating chair that can also move on command.

deck: Farina is a cardinal.
description:
Origin

A cardinal of the Christian faith, Farina was to be escorted up north from Iskfold to the Hammaruskk coast. Magnus the Black accepted the task.

Major Story Arcs

Days into his travel with Magnus the Black, they were attacked by a group of armed men. Overpowered, Magnus was unable to prevent the men from killing Cardinal Farina. Left for dead, Magnus was found and nursed back to health by Julia, the adopted daughter of Farina. She asked him to go escort her north in Farina's place.
name: Farina

deck: Kitta is a blacksmith in Iskfold, Norway.
description:
Origin

Kitta is from Moorish descent and was an assassin for hire in Frankia, Norway. She later becomes a blacksmith in Iskfold. She stashes the weaponry of Magnus the Black. She provides him with new weapons, if he has money.

Major Story Arcs

While escorting Julia across the Black Road, Magnus suddenly remembers he had seen Kitta in the battle against enemy soldiers that killed his wife. Telling this to Julia, she points out to Magnus they're being followed by the same Kitta. Suddenly, Julia turns on Magnus and shoots him several times with her crossbow. She escapes north. Kitta takes care of Magnus and offers to join him in tracking down Julia.

deck: Icelandic member of a group of metahumans.
description:
Creation

Writer Simon Spurrier has revealed he got the idea of Ottar from the Hyndluljoo, the "Lay of Hyndla", from the Poetic Edda. It chronicles the more racier parts of the myths and legends of the Norse religion. The hero of the tale, Ottar the Simple, pleads with Freya to help him learn about his ancestry, which she achieves by smuggling him into the lair of the giant seeress Hyndla. She does so by turning him into a Hildisvini, a battle pig. Ottar and Freya were said to be lovers.

Powers & Abilities

Ottar is able to transform into a 'battle pig', a giant boar-like creature, who is impervious to bullets.
